Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{} on medium-high heat.

Fry the @Tomato Puree{30%grams} and garlic until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Slow Cooked British Chicken{290%grams} along with the juices from the packet, stir in the
@Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Chipotle Paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and
@Water for the Sauce{100%ml}.

> See pantry for water amount.

Simmer on low with the lid on until tender enough to shred with a #fork{}, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT:
Ensure the chicken is piping hot throughout.

In the meantime, stack your @Plain Taco Tortillas{6} into a pile and cut into 8 triangles.

Place on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle with @oil{drizzle}. TIP: Use two
baking trays if necessary.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle over the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}.

Bake on the top shelf in the oven until lightly golden brown and crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}. TIP: Keep
an eye on them to make sure they colour evenly.

Meanwhile, halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop out the flesh
onto a board. Cut into 1cm chunks.

Add to a small #bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the chicken is tender, remove the lid and shred the chicken with two #forks{}. Stir through
the @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Butter{20%grams} (see pantry for both amounts).

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then remove from the heat.

Transfer your spiced nachos to one side of your #serving bowls{}.

Serve the pulled chicken alongside. Top with the avocado chunks.

Sprinkle over the cheese to finish.

Enjoy!